_header: O ye my emperess I your servant this to you say
_description: Humphrey Newton, A love letter to his mistress — twelve quatrains

BodLatMisC66.First Lines:
O ye my emperice I your seruaunt þis to you I saymy derist
                    qwene the whiche is makeles…
BodLatMisC66.Last Lines:
…O ye my hert be ye stidfast & trulofe kepeye are my trist
                    my tresoure ye may be cald kyndenes
BodLatMisC66.Editions:
Robbins,  Rossell Hope. 
             “The Poems of Humphrey Newton, Esquire, 1466-1536.” 
             PMLA
